{"parse":{"title":"Chartered Physicist","pageid":19177967,"revid":825244473,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Chartered Physicist</b> (<b>CPhys</b>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_(professional)\" title=\"Chartered (professional)\">chartered status</a> and a <a href=\"/wiki/Professional_qualification\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Professional qualification\">professional qualification</a> awarded by the <a href=\"/wiki/Institute_of_Physics\" title=\"Institute of Physics\">Institute of Physics</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It is denoted by the postnominals \"CPhys\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Achieving chartered status in any profession denotes to the wider community a high level of specialised subject knowledge and professional competence. According to the Institute of Physics, holders of the award of the Chartered Physicist (CPhys) demonstrate the \"highest standards of professionalism, up-to-date expertise, quality and safety\" along with \"the capacity to undertake independent practice and exercise leadership\" as well as \"commitment to keep pace with advancing knowledge and with the increasing expectations and requirements for which any profession must take responsibility\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-CPhys_guidelines_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CPhys_guidelines-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The status of Chartered Physicist was introduced in 1985 following approval from the <a href=\"/wiki/Privy_Council_(UK)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Privy Council (UK)\">Privy Council</a>. It was originally granted  automatically with corporate membership of the Institute of Physics (IoP).<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Reform of the membership structure in 1998 saw Chartered Physicist established as a separate qualification from 2001 that could be gained either alongside or after the status of Member or Fellow of the IoP. In order to gain the qualification, a physicist must be appropriately qualified (an accredited MSci or <a href=\"/wiki/MPhys\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MPhys\">MPhys</a> integrated master's degree is standard, although experience leading to an equivalent level can be counted), have had a minimum of two years of structured training and a minimum of two years responsible work experience, have demonstrated a commitment to continuing professional development, and have gained a number of competencies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> For physicists gaining the status from 2012, revalidation through proof of <a href=\"/wiki/Continuing_professional_development\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Continuing professional development\">continuing professional development</a> is required every three years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-CPhys_guidelines_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CPhys_guidelines-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Chartered Physicist is considered to be equal in status to <a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Engineer_(UK)\" title=\"Chartered Engineer (UK)\">Chartered Engineer</a>, which the IoP also awards as a member of the <a href=\"/wiki/Engineering_Council_UK\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Engineering Council UK\">Engineering Council UK</a>, and other chartered statuses in the UK.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> It is also considered a \"regulated profession\" under the <a href=\"/wiki/European_professional_qualification_directives\" title=\"European professional qualification directives\">European professional qualification directives</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chartered_Physicist&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Engineer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chartered Engineer\">Chartered Engineer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Scientist\" title=\"Chartered Scientist\">Chartered Scientist</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Chemist\" title=\"Chartered Chemist\">Chartered Chemist</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/European_Engineer\" title=\"European Engineer\">European Engineer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/European_Chemist\" title=\"European Chemist\">European Chemist</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chartered_Physicist&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://nationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk/advice/planning/jobprofiles/Pages/physicist.aspx\">\"Job profiles: Physicist\"</a>. <i>National Careers Service</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 May</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=National+Careers+Service&amp;rft.atitle=Job+profiles%3A+Physicist&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk%2Fadvice%2Fplanning%2Fjobprofiles%2FPages%2Fphysicist.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=VkqCBAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PR17#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>Titles and Forms of Address: A Guide to Correct Use</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Bloomsbury_Publishing\" title=\"Bloomsbury Publishing\">Bloomsbury Publishing</a>. 10 October 2014. p.&#160;xvii.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Titles+and+Forms+of+Address%3A+A+Guide+to+Correct+Use&amp;rft.pages=xvii&amp;rft.pub=Bloomsbury+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2014-10-10&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DVkqCBAAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPR17%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-CPhys_guidelines-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-CPhys_guidelines_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-CPhys_guidelines_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iop.org/membership/char-sta/chartership/cphys/page_51812.html\">\"Chartered Physicist (CPhys)\"</a>. Institute of Physics<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 May</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Chartered+Physicist+%28CPhys%29&amp;rft.pub=Institute+of+Physics&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iop.org%2Fmembership%2Fchar-sta%2Fchartership%2Fcphys%2Fpage_51812.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">John L. Lewis (1 January 1999). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=NtMiBPgdF6cC&amp;pg=PA183#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>125 Years: The Physical Society &amp; The Institute of Physics</i></a>. CRC Press. p.&#160;183.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=125+Years%3A+The+Physical+Society+%26+The+Institute+of+Physics&amp;rft.pages=183&amp;rft.pub=CRC+Press&amp;rft.date=1999-01-01&amp;rft.au=John+L.+Lewis&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DNtMiBPgdF6cC%26pg%3DPA183%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iop.org/about/royal_charter/file_38390.pdf\">\"Charter and Bylaws\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. Institute of Physics<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 May</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Charter+and+Bylaws&amp;rft.pub=Institute+of+Physics&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iop.org%2Fabout%2Froyal_charter%2Ffile_38390.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iop.org/membership/char-sta/chartership/why/file_38066.pdf\">\"Becoming Chartered by the Institute \u2013 Frequently Asked Questions\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. Institute of Physics<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 May</span> 2016</span>. <q>[Q]Which one [Chartered Physicist or Chartered Engineer] is best? [A] None of the standards are better or worse than any other. They are just suitable for different people.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Becoming+Chartered+by+the+Institute+%E2%80%93+Frequently+Asked+Questions&amp;rft.pub=Institute+of+Physics&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iop.org%2Fmembership%2Fchar-sta%2Fchartership%2Fwhy%2Ffile_38066.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmselect/cmeduc/uc371-i/uc37101.htm\">\"Oral evidence taken before the education committee\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/House_of_Commons\" title=\"House of Commons\">House of Commons</a>. 27 July 2013. Q16<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 May</span> 2016</span>. <q>'When I set the chartered science teacher up, I linked it to chartered scientist, which is exactly the same as chartered physicist or chartered engineer, so that nobody could turn round and say, \"What you are doing is below the standard of any other chartered status.\"' (Professor Derek Bell, College of Teachers)</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Oral+evidence+taken+before+the+education+committee&amp;rft.pages=Q16&amp;rft.pub=House+of+Commons&amp;rft.date=2013-07-27&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fpublications.parliament.uk%2Fpa%2Fcm201314%2Fcmselect%2Fcmeduc%2Fuc371-i%2Fuc37101.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Kate Parker (7 October 2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://eandt.theiet.org/content/articles/2016/10/professional-development-for-engineers-expand-your-mind/\">\"Professional development for engineers: expand your mind\"</a>. <i>Engineering &amp; Technology</i>. <a href=\"/wiki/Institution_of_Engineering_and_Technology\" title=\"Institution of Engineering and Technology\">Institution of Engineering and Technology</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 May</span> 2017</span>. <q>Since engineering covers a multitude of disciplines and professions, several different professional statuses exist to reflect the extensive array of skills and competences within them all. The main chartered qualifications are Chartered Engineer (CEng) and Chartered Physicist (CPhys). Engineers can also register as an Engineering Technician (EngTech), Incorporated Engineer (IEng), or ICT Technician (ICTTech).</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Engineering+%26+Technology&amp;rft.atitle=Professional+development+for+engineers%3A+expand+your+mind&amp;rft.date=2016-10-07&amp;rft.au=Kate+Parker&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Feandt.theiet.org%2Fcontent%2Farticles%2F2016%2F10%2Fprofessional-development-for-engineers-expand-your-mind%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://ec.europa.eu/growth/tools-databases/regprof/index.cfm?action=regprof&amp;id_regprof=1048&amp;tab=general\">\"Chartered physicist (United Kingdom)\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/European_Commission\" title=\"European Commission\">European Commission</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 May</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Chartered+physicist+%28United+Kingdom%29&amp;rft.pub=European+Commission&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fgrowth%2Ftools-databases%2Fregprof%2Findex.cfm%3Faction%3Dregprof%26id_regprof%3D1048%26tab%3Dgeneral&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChartered+Physicist\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1330\nCached time: 20180908170230\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.112 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.133 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 369/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 15183/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 83/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 10443/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wiki